53 per cent of the patients admitted to the Victor Gadbua shelter come from home and 47 per cent from the hospital.
Access to palliative care
It is believed that 77 per cent of Canadians simply do not have access to palliative care, i.e. care, which is provided to alleviate the suffering of patients who have entered the final stage of their lives, either at home, in a hospital or in a shelter.
