- I thought I was gonna die in this cage."
While in Quantico, Manning, he said, spent most of his time in a small cell - at least 21 hours, and often more than 23 hours a day - all alone.
Manning reports that he was only allowed to leave a mattress, a blanket, a slab, a few items of clothing, and a pair of glasses.
He says he was trying to move, as sleeping or even just lying down during the daytime prohibited the rules.
