If the guards didn't see his face when he was in bed at night, he said he was waken up and forced to turn on his back.
Manning's lawyer filed a formal objection to Manning's ill-treatment in January 2011.
In April 2011, Manning was transferred to a military prison in Fort Levenworth, Kansas.
In addition, on Friday, the judge interrogated Manning about the statement he made during his statement on Thursday that, after he was forced to sleep naked in his cell in Quantico one night, he was forced to stand naked in front of the guards and other prisoners during the morning check.
